<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Child Development Theory Lab</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; max-width: 800px; margin: 20px auto; padding: 20px; background: #f4f7f6; }
        .card { background: white; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); margin-bottom: 20px; }
        button { background: #007bff; color: white; border: none; padding: 10px 15px; border-radius: 4px; cursor: pointer; }
        #feedback { font-weight: bold; margin-top: 10px; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Child Development Theory Lab</h1>
    <p>As a future educator, you must recognize the theoretical basis of student behavior. Match the theory to the classroom scenario below.</p>

    <div class="card">
        <h3 id="scenario">Scenario: A student struggles with a math problem, so you provide a "scaffold" or hint to help them solve it just beyond their current independent ability.</h3>
        <select id="theorySelect">
            <option value="">--Select a Theory--</option>
            <option value="Piaget">Piaget's Cognitive Development</option>
            <option value="Vygotsky">Vygotsky's Zone of Proximal Development</option>
            <option value="Erikson">Erikson's Psychosocial Stages</option>
        </select>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer()">Submit</button>
        <div id="feedback"></div>
    </div>

    <script>
        function checkAnswer() {
            const select = document.getElementById('theorySelect').value;
            const feedback = document.getElementById('feedback');
            if (select === "Vygotsky") {
                feedback.innerText = "Correct! Vygotsky emphasized that social interaction and support (scaffolding) are essential for learning within the Zone of Proximal Development.";
                feedback.style.color = "green";
            } else if (select === "") {
                feedback.innerText = "Please select an option.";
            } else {
                feedback.innerText = "Not quite. Think about the 'help' provided. This focuses on the gap between what a child can do alone vs. with guidance.";
                feedback.style.color = "red";
            }
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
